-- Sakakibara Says Yen to Reach Record, More Intervention Risks U.S. Rebuke
-- B y   S h i g e k i   N o z a w a
-- 2010-09-21T08:01:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/sakakibara-says-yen-to-reach-record-more-intervention-risks-u-s-rebuke.html
The yen will reach a record high
against the dollar this year and attempts by Japan to stem gains
may be criticized by the U.S., said Eisuke Sakakibara, formerly
Japan’s top currency official.  Intervention in currency markets should be avoided as a
rule, Sakakibara said in an interview today in Tokyo. A strong
currency can be beneficial, he said.  Japan intervened to weaken the yen last week for the first
time since 2004. Sakakibara became known as “Mr. Yen” during
his 1997-1999 tenure at the Ministry of Finance for his efforts
to influence the yen rate through verbal and actual intervention
in the currency markets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
